 A former lecturer in the Department of English language at the University of Ilorin (UNILORIN), Prof Mohammed Idiagbon, is dead. Prof. Idiagbon was said to have died early yesterday morning in Ilorin, Kwara State, after a brief illness. The deceased was on a one-year sabbatical at the Kwara State University (KWASU) Malete in 2013. Idiagbon was the former president of the Balogun Fulani Youth Development Constituency in Ilorin. Head of English Department at KWASU Dr. Moshood Zakariya confirmed Idiagbonâ€™s death. 